---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Vol. I, No. I"
  description="A Naturalist's Record of an Investigation from First Principles to the Frontier of Quantum Gravity. Vol. I, No. I."
>
  <a href="#main" class="skip">Skip to contents</a>

  <div class="page">

    <header class="masthead">
      <div class="masthead-corners">
        <span>No. I</span>
        <span>Bend &middot; Oregon</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="masthead-title">
        <span class="masthead-title-main">The Donkey</span>
        <span class="masthead-title-conn">on the</span>
        <span class="masthead-title-main">Edge</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="masthead-strap">
        A Naturalist's Record of an Investigation from First Principles<br />
        to the Frontier of Quantum Gravity.
      </p>
      <div class="masthead-line">
        <span class="masthead-line-rule"></span>
        <span class="masthead-meta">
          <span>Vol. I</span>
          <span class="dot"></span>
          <span>No. I</span>
          <span class="dot"></span>
          <span>May MMXXVI</span>
        </span>
        <span class="masthead-line-rule"></span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main id="main">

      <section class="frontispiece" aria-label="Frontispiece">
        <figure class="plate">
          <div class="plate-inner">
            <img src="/images/donkeyedge.png" alt="A donkey upon the edge of the investigation." width="800" height="600" />
          </div>
        </figure>
        <figcaption class="plate-caption">
          <span class="fig">Fig. I.</span> Donkey upon the Edge of the Investigation.<br />
          Drawn from life, April MMXXVI.
        </figcaption>
      </section>

      <section class="intro" aria-labelledby="intro-head">
        <div class="intro-head" id="intro-head">
          <span>Introductory Note</span>
        </div>
        <p class="intro-body">
          A non-physicist and an artificial intelligence walked from <em>Physics&nbsp;101</em> to the frontier of <em>quantum gravity</em>, and wrote a paper. The investigation occupied eighteen days, from the twenty-third of April to the eleventh of May in the year MMXXVI. The paper is at arXiv. The full record, here below, comprises the curriculum that was traversed, the research that was conducted, the methodology by which it was made, and the current state of the laboratory.
        </p>
        <div class="intro-after" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="intro-after-rule"></span>
          <span class="intro-after-mark">&#10086;</span>
          <span class="intro-after-rule"></span>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="contents" aria-labelledby="contents-head">
        <header class="contents-head">
          <h2 class="contents-head-title" id="contents-head">Contents of this Volume</h2>
          <p class="contents-head-sub">five articles, with appendices</p>
        </header>

        <a href="/paper" class="toc-entry">
          <span class="toc-num">I.</span>
          <div class="toc-body">
            <h3 class="toc-title">The Paper</h3>
            <p class="toc-sub">Complexity-Sensitive Complementarity in Non-Isometric Holographic Codes.</p>
            <p class="toc-desc">Five results, three figures, thirty-eight references. Posted to arXiv on the eleventh of May, MMXXVI.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="toc-page">Read &nbsp;&sect; I</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/curriculum" class="toc-entry">
          <span class="toc-num">II.</span>
          <div class="toc-body">
            <h3 class="toc-title">The Curriculum</h3>
            <p class="toc-sub">Thirty-eight reference documents, from Physics&nbsp;101 to the frontier.</p>
            <p class="toc-desc">The full path of study, mapped as a subway diagram, with prerequisites and dependencies for each station along the way.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="toc-page">Read &nbsp;&sect; II</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/field-notes" class="toc-entry">
          <span class="toc-num">III.</span>
          <div class="toc-body">
            <h3 class="toc-title">Field Notes</h3>
            <p class="toc-sub">The plain-English record of an eighteen-day walk.</p>
            <p class="toc-desc">Ten work posts and eight essays. The texture of doing real research, with the failures visible and the catches documented.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="toc-page">Read &nbsp;&sect; III</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/method" class="toc-entry">
          <span class="toc-num">IV.</span>
          <div class="toc-body">
            <h3 class="toc-title">The Method</h3>
            <p class="toc-sub">On the doing of this sort of work, and on its doing again.</p>
            <p class="toc-desc">The thesis. The protocol. The failure modes. The calibration log. The guide for other generalists.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="toc-page">Read &nbsp;&sect; IV</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/lab" class="toc-entry">
          <span class="toc-num">V.</span>
          <div class="toc-body">
            <h3 class="toc-title">The Laboratory</h3>
            <p class="toc-sub">Continuing investigations, and what is happening <em>now</em>.</p>
            <p class="toc-desc">The Paper 2 plan. The code and data. Updates as they happen, with the original predictions kept on the record.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="toc-page">Read &nbsp;&sect; V</span>
        </a>
      </section>

      <aside class="dispatches" aria-labelledby="dispatches-head">
        <div class="dispatches-frame">
          <span class="dispatches-corner dispatches-corner-left">
            <span class="dispatches-corner-text">Latest</span>
          </span>
          <span class="dispatches-corner dispatches-corner-right">
            <span class="dispatches-corner-text">Dispatches</span>
          </span>
          <h3 class="dispatches-head" id="dispatches-head">From the Wire</h3>
          <div class="dispatches-rule" aria-hidden="true">
            <span class="dispatches-rule-line"></span>
            <span class="dispatches-rule-mark">&#10086;</span>
            <span class="dispatches-rule-line"></span>
          </div>
          <p class="dispatches-body">
            Phase 8 of the research <em>begins this week</em>. The <a href="/lab/roadmap">Paper 2 plan</a> has been made public. The author awaits arXiv number assignment.
          </p>
          <div class="dispatches-foot">
            <span class="pulse" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            Updated MMXXVI &middot; V &middot; XI
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </main>

    <footer class="colophon">
      <span class="colophon-mark">Colophon</span>
      <div class="colophon-inner">
        <figure class="colophon-portrait">
          <img src="/images/donkeyportrait.png" alt="" aria-hidden="true" />
        </figure>
        <h2 class="colophon-byline">Adam R. Cagle</h2>
        <p class="colophon-role">Editor &amp; Author</p>
        <p class="colophon-with">
          with <em>Claude</em> of Anthropic, in the role of computational collaborator.
        </p>
        <div class="colophon-rule" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="colophon-rule-line"></span>
          <span class="colophon-rule-mark">&#8258;</span>
          <span class="colophon-rule-line"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="colophon-notes">
          <p>
            Composed at Bend, in the State of Oregon, in the months of April and May, in the Year of Our Lord Two Thousand and Twenty-Six.
          </p>
          <p>
            Set in <em>IM Fell DW Pica</em> for display matter, <em>Old Standard</em> for the body, and <em>JetBrains Mono</em> for the technical apparatus. Illustrations executed in pen and ink.
          </p>
        </div>
        <nav class="colophon-links" aria-label="Footer links">
          <a href="/about">About</a>
          <a href="/about#citation">Cite this work</a>
          <a href="mailto:adamrcagle@gmail.com">Correspondence</a>
          <a href="/paper">arXiv</a>
        </nav>
        <p class="colophon-meta">&copy; MMXXVI</p>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </div>
</Base>
